A man of the Egyptians living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at Jer.37.5
Another name of par.oh (פַּרְעֹה "Pharaoh" H6547R)
Combined with par.oh (פַּרְעֹה "Pharaoh" H6547R)
§ Pharaoh = "great house"
the common title of the king of Egypt

vocabinfos.mediumDef:
A man of the Egyptians living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Ki.23.29; also called Pharaoh at 2Ki.23.35 etc.;
Another name of ne.kho (נְכוֹ "Neco" H5224)
§ Pharaoh = "great house"
the common title of the king of Egypt
